Functions

U16 RXN_Debug_Information (const U08 prn, const RXN_constel_t constel, RXN_debug_information_t *information)
 Get the seed information for last call to RXN_Generate_Assistance().

Detailed Description

Defines the structures and functions to access debug information.

These functions are supplemental to the main API functions and are intended to provide more information for troubleshooting purposes. They are not required for the normal operation of the system.

Since:
1.1.0

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum RXN_debug_code_t

An enumeration of all the available debug codes used throughout the library.

The codes are separated into the following categories:

  • OK
  • RESERVED
  • INFO
  • WARN
  • ERROR

With the exception of OK (0), the rest of the categories are organized into sets of numerical ranges bounded by the following DEFINE constants:

  • RXN_DEBUG_CODE_RESERVED_RANGE_BEGIN --> RXN_DEBUG_CODE_RESERVED_RANGE_END
  • RXN_DEBUG_CODE_INFO_RANGE_BEGIN --> RXN_DEBUG_CODE_INFO_RANGE_END
  • RXN_DEBUG_CODE_WARN_RANGE_BEGIN --> RXN_DEBUG_CODE_WARN_RANGE_END
  • RXN_DEBUG_CODE_ERROR_RANGE_BEGIN --> RXN_DEBUG_CODE_ERROR_RANGE_END
Remarks:
Please note the enumeration value may change in the future as more codes are added. The names are sorted to aid reading and usability. Always refer to the enumeration name in the code (instead of the int value) to avoid compatibilities problem when migrating to a future version.
Since:
1.2.0

Function Documentation

U16 RXN_Debug_Information ( const U08  prn,
const RXN_constel_t  constel,
RXN_debug_information_t *  information 
)

Get the seed information for last call to RXN_Generate_Assistance().

Parameters:
prn [IN] The PRN to generate or update a prediction buffer for. Data is calculated and stored independantly for each PRN.
constel [IN] Constellation for which to produce assistance (optinal param). Default GPS. Glonass not yet supported
Returns:
RXN_SUCCESS If the function completes successfully.
RXN_FAIL If the function fails.

Description
This function returns the seed information associated with the last function call. The information provides additional information for debugging the operation of the library. You should call the function immediately when a function's return value indicates that such a call will return useful data.

Parameters:
information [OUT] A pointer to a RXN_debug_information_t that will be updated with data from the most recent operation. The information provides a snapshot of persisted data.

Applicable Standards
Proprietary to GPStream (tm) PGPS (tm) client software, SAGPS (tm) client software and GPStream (tm) PGPS (tm) server.

Attention:
This function is useful for troubleshooting problems with RXN_Generate_Assistance() and RXN_Get_Ephemeris().
See also:
RXN_Debug_Message()
Since:
1.2.0
